    "finding": "When candidate answers use entirely novel vocabulary (true paraphrases), the pipeline struggles to distinguish quality levels. SBERT similarity and keyword coverage both fail because MiniLM-L6-v2 was trained on general text, not interview-specific semantic equivalence. This motivates future work: fine-tuning SBERT on interview QA pairs or using larger models (e.g., all-mpnet-base-v2) for better paraphrase detection.",
    "implication_for_real_use": "The system works best when candidates use domain-specific terminology from the ideal answer. For candidates who explain concepts in completely novel ways, the system underscores their answers. This is a known limitation of embedding-based evaluation and motivates fine-tuning as future work."
